    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Global Greenhouse</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bela Liptak letter points out that moving manufacturing to less regulated regions beyond US borders has increased total generation of greenhouse gases on planet (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>John Podesta, President Clinton's chief of staff, defends the administration's record on global warming (letter, Jan. 10). But it is true that economic globalization, and the resulting shift of manufacturing to less regulated regions beyond our borders, has increased the total generation of greenhouse gases on our planet.</p>
        <p>BELA LIPTAK  Stamford, Conn., Jan. 10, 2001</p>
      </block>
